13/09/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Both the British presidency of the EU and the US administration have welcomed the election of the new government in Albania, while urging the acceleration of reforms. In separate statements from the British and US embassies on Monday (12 September), officials called on the coalition cabinet led by Prime Minister Sali Berisha to begin work immediately on implementing reforms that would bring the country closer to the EU and NATO, as well as to step the fight against crime and corruption. 
Also Monday, Tirana Mayor Edi Rama officially confirmed that he would run for the post of Socialist Party (SP) leader. Following its defeat in the July parliamentary elections, SP chairman Fatos Nano announced his resignation. (Albanian News - 13/09/05)
